label: NA
definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing MeasurementorFact data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the 'MeasurementorFact' table in the database (.accdb) file.

label: eventID
definition: Global unique identifier assigned to an Event (something that occurs at a place and time, such as a survey or measurement).

label: measurementDeterminedBy
definition: The acronym for the monitoring program from which this measurement originated.

label: measurementID
definition: Global unique identifier assigned to the variable/measurementType.

label: measurementMethod
definition: A description of or reference to (publication, URI) the method or protocol used to determine the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
examples: URL of the MonitoringResources.rog field and if avilable calcuation method

label: measurementRemarks
definition: Comments or notes accompanying the MeasurementOrFact.

label: measurementType
definition: The variable or name of the measurement.

label: measurementValue
definition: The value of the measurementTerm attribute measured in units given in the measurementTerm definitions.

label: resultID
definition: Unique global identifier for each result measurement.

label: resultTypeCV
definition: The category of measurement type to which the measurement belongs. This is the same category as that in the 'measurementType' attribute in the MetricCV table.
examples: tail length, "temperature", "trap line length", "survey area", "trap type"
